The history processing for Base ClearCase executes the following command:

{code}
cleartool lshistory -fmt %Nd###%o###%u###'%c'###%Xn -nco -r <vob_path>
{code}

where 'vob_path' is the top level directory for the VOB (eg. if the VOB is \some_vob, then 'vob_path' will be 'some_vob').

However, in situations where the VOB is multi-part (ie. \vobs\some_vob), FE is attempting to use 'vobs\some_vob' as the 'vob_path', whereas it should be using 'some_vob'.

