I was working on an event listener plugin recently that did some tasks in a worker thread. This failed at runtime with an IllegalStateException. After some poking around, I figured out that I need to do something like this:

try {
Disposer.pushThreadInstance();
work();
}
finally { Disposer.popThreadInstance(); }

if I access the fisheye SPI from that thread.

We need to either isolate plugin developers from this or document it clearly. It's not something that we want people to stumble over.

